<li id="cite_note-32"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">British Museum Collection Database; Tait 43; Robinson, 87</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cherry, 50–51, with photo of the Vienna copy</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-34"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Tait, 42</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-35"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-35">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cherry, 50; Tait, 43</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-36"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cherry, 15, with photo showing the doors opened on p. 14; Tait, 26–27, who calls the sheet vellum.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-37"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-37">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">British Museum Collection Database; Cherry, 34; Tait 26</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-38"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-38">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cherry, 25</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-39"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cherry, 44–47</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-40"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-40">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Strictly <i>email en ronde bosse</i>; in French <i>ronde bosse</i> equates to "free-standing" in English, and may be used of any sculpture that is so.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-41"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-41">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cherry, 26–37</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-42"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-42">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Robinson (2008), 87</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-43"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-43">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Tait, 43; Anderson, 167-168; for other examples in wood see <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:KunstpalastDSCF6424.jpg" title="File:KunstpalastDSCF6424.jpg">this angel</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:KunstpalastDSCF6426.jpg" title="File:KunstpalastDSCF6426.jpg">his companion</a> in Düsseldorf.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-44"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-44">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Tait 42–43 (quoted); Cherry, 34; British Museum Collection Database</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-45"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-45">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Stein</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-46"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-46">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Henderson, 134–139; Snyder, 16–17, and chapter 3 on the patronage of the brothers</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-47"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-47">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Tait, 37</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-48"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-48">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cherry, 44, 47–48; Tait, 36–39</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-49"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-49">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Henderson, 134–136, quotation p. 135</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-50"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Tait, 39; Cherry, 27–28, with photograph. Online image <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.history.ac.uk/richardII/stmichael.html">here</a>, from <i>Richard II's Treasure; the Riches of a Medieval King</i>, from The Institute of Historical Research and Royal Holloway, University of London.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-51"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cherry, 43–44; Tait, 37</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-52"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cherry, 19–21</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-53"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-53">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Robinson (2008), 87; <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.britishmuseum.org/explore/highlights/highlight_objects/pe_mla/r/reliquary_pendant,_holy_thorn.aspx">Reliquary pendant of the Holy Thorn</a>, British Museum Highlights, accessed May 27, 2011</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-54"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-54">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.britishmuseum.org/research/search_the_collection_database/search_object_details.aspx?objectid=48782&partid=1">Wood and leather case</a> British Museum Collection Database, accessed June 16, 2010. Registration number: 1892,0501.2</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-55"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The Vienna "Lover's Brooch" discussed by Tait, 38 and 50</span></li>
</ol>
</div>
